      "content": "exactly. and what's crazy is that it's not just accidental stuff. when you look at the way the delays are structured in specific high-volume nodes, it looks coded. like the metadata isn't just describing the transaction, it is the asset. it's a way to move trillions without a single cent actually \"moving\" on a bank's books. how would a system even begin to track or tax something that exists only in the structural noise of the network?",
